data.title: Haylie Duff Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Haylie Duff with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Studied ballet from an early age in Texas

Prime-time guest appearances early in her acting career included Chicago Hope, Boston Public and Third Watch

Co-wrote two songs on sister Hilary's 2003 debut album, Metamorphosis, as well as one track on her 2007 release, Dignity

Joined Hilary to portray the Shangri-Las on an episode of NBC's American Dreams in 2003

Appeared in commercials for Mattel's Barbie and Hershey's Ice Breakers

Enrolled in the Harvard Extension School through the Distance Learning Program in 2005

Starred in two movies from the Hallmark Channel's popular Love Comes Softly Saga in 2009, Love Finds a Home and Love Takes Wing
